## Request

```bash
curl https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1/images/generations \
  -H "x-api-key: $BYTESPIKE_API_KEY" \
  -H "content-type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "model": "{/* model_id */}",
    "prompt": "A koi pond at dusk, ink-wash style, soft purple sky",
    "size": "{/* 1024x1024 / 2048x2048 / 1024x1536 / etc. */}",
    "n": 1
  }'
```

### Body parameters

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `model` | string | yes | — | `{/* model_id */}` |
| `prompt` | string | yes | — | {/* "CJK accepted natively" / "English-only" */} |
| `size` | string | no | {/* 1024x1024 */} | Supported: {/* list, e.g. "1024x1024, 1024x1536, 1536x1024" */} |
| `n` | integer | no | 1 | 1–{/* 4 */} images per call. Each billed separately. |
| `seed` | integer | no | — | Reproducibility. {/* "Supported" / "Not supported" */} |
| `negative_prompt` | string | no | — | {/* "Standard SD-style negation" / "Not supported" */} |
| `quality` | string | no | {/* standard */} | {/* e.g. "standard / hd" — delete row if not applicable */} |
| `style` | string | no | — | {/* delete row if not applicable */} |
| `image_init` | string | no | — | {/* URL of init image for img2img — delete if not supported */} |
| `{/* model-specific */} ` | {/* type */} | no | — | {/* e.g. `aspect_ratio` for some Google models */} |

## Response

```json
{
  "created": 1715174400,
  "data": [
    {
      "url": "https://cdn.bytespike.ai/img/{/* … */}",
      "revised_prompt": "{/* model's interpretation of the prompt */}"
    }
  ]
}
```

Image URLs are pre-signed, valid for **24 hours**. Download and rehost if
you need long-term storage.

### Response fields

| Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `created` | integer | Unix timestamp. |
| `data[].url` | string | Pre-signed CDN URL, 24h expiry. |
| `data[].revised_prompt` | string | {/* "Always present" / "Only when model rewrites" */} |
| `data[].b64_json` | string | {/* delete if not supported */} |

Headers always present on every response (success + failure):

```
X-RateLimit-Limit: {/* USD cap, e.g. 50.00 */}
X-RateLimit-Remaining: {/* USD remaining, e.g. 42.18 */}
X-RateLimit-Reset: {/* Unix ts, e.g. 1716705600 */}
X-Quota-Remaining-Credits: {/* USD lifetime remaining, e.g. 192.40 */}
```

Per-call cost via [`/api/v1/me/usage`](/api-reference/account/me-usage).

## Code examples

<CodeGroup>

```bash cURL
curl https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1/images/generations \
  -H "x-api-key: $BYTESPIKE_API_KEY" \
  -H "content-type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "model": "{/* model_id */}",
    "prompt": "A koi pond at dusk, ink-wash style, soft purple sky",
    "size": "{/* 1024x1024 */}",
    "n": 1
  }'
```

```python Python
import openai

client = openai.OpenAI(
    base_url="https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1",
    api_key="$BYTESPIKE_API_KEY",
)

response = client.images.generate(
    model="{/* model_id */}",
    prompt="A koi pond at dusk, ink-wash style, soft purple sky",
    size="{/* 1024x1024 */}",
    n=1,
)

print(response.data[0].url)
```

```javascript Node
import OpenAI from "openai"

const client = new OpenAI({
  baseURL: "https://llm.bytespike.ai/v1",
  apiKey: process.env.BYTESPIKE_API_KEY,
})

const response = await client.images.generate({
  model: "{/* model_id */}",
  prompt: "A koi pond at dusk, ink-wash style, soft purple sky",
  size: "{/* 1024x1024 */}",
  n: 1,
})

console.log(response.data[0].url)
```

</CodeGroup>

## Errors

| Code | Trigger | Billed? |
|---|---|---|
| 400 | Body validation (size unsupported, prompt empty) | No |
| 401 | Missing / revoked key | No |
| 402 | Wallet exhausted | No |
| 403 | Scope denied / IP not allowlisted | No |
| 413 | Prompt too long | No |
| 422 | Param not supported by this model | No |
| 429 | Rate-limited | No |
| 451 | Prompt blocked by upstream safety filter | No |
| 5xx | Upstream provider issue | No (auto-retry envelope) |

See [Error Handling](/concepts/error-handling) for the full enum.

